# CODE REPO INSPECTION

For core papers that the idea builds on or competes with, agents are **encouraged to clone and inspect code repos** for deeper understanding:

```bash
# Clone to temp directory
git clone <repo_url> /tmp/idea_refinery_<method_name>

# Inspect training configs, model architecture, resource requirements
# Look for: batch size, # GPUs, training time, dataset sizes, model params

# Clean up when done
rm -rf /tmp/idea_refinery_<method_name>
```

**When to clone:**
- Estimating resource requirements (check training configs)
- Understanding exact method details not clear from paper
- Checking if existing code can be reused/adapted
- Verifying that a claimed result is reproducible (check issues, code quality)

